The paper presents a search engine that combines full-text search and ontology search, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) applications. The paper also discusses the query language, index, natural language processing, and user interface, which are relevant to database (DB), computational linguistics (CL), and machine learning (LG) subfields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
